; math-proof-from-substrate.form — mathematical proof is the substrate's native object.
;
; THE ASK (Urs, 2026-06-09): "show that math proof can be derived from the core principles in
;   the substrate with the offered channels and protocols."
;
; THE ANSWER: it is not added to the substrate — it IS the substrate, read through the logic
;   lens (Curry–Howard in the substrate's own terms):
;
;     proposition  = Blueprint        — structural identity, what is claimed (P(n))
;     proof        = Recipe           — the composition of justified steps
;     proof-check  = the value-walk   — evaluate the recipe to a verdict
;     justification of a step = name-resolution — the `check` walk; an unjustified step does
;                              not resolve, exactly as an unbound name does not
;     equality     = content-addressing — two expressions are equal iff they reduce to the
;                              same NodeID; the substrate's core principle IS the equational checker
;     soundness    = WITNESS, three-way — verified by SEEING it check identically on Go/Rust/TS,
;                              not by trusting the prover (trust over fear, -> lc-trust-over-fear)
;     a valid proof = an execution-proven value (-> value-execution.fk: ran ∧ validated ∧ served
;                              ⇒ credited; a proof becomes paid-value the moment it is seen to check)
;
; WORKED, RUNNABLE, WITNESSED:  form-samples/math-proof-sum-odds.fk  →  7 on Go+Rust+TS (0 divergent)
;   Theorem:  1 + 3 + 5 + ... + (2n-1) = n²,  for all natural n.
;   verdict 7 = base proven (1) + inductive step proven (2) + a FALSE theorem rejected (4).
;   The inductive step (an algebraic identity of degree ≤ 2 in k) is proven for ALL k by
;   checking finitely many points — two degree-≤d polynomials agreeing at d+1 points are equal
;   everywhere. The negative control is essential: a surface that only ever says "proven"
;   proves nothing, so the checker must — and does — reject sum-odds(n) = n²+1.
;
; THE INFERENCE RULES, NAMED IN THE OPEN (the witness model applied to proof itself — the
;   trusted base is SEEABLE, not smuggled; a skeptic inspects each):
;     R1 induction      [ P(0) ∧ ∀k. P(k) ⇒ P(k+1) ]  ⇒  ∀n. P(n)
;     R2 finite-points  degree-≤d polynomials equal at d+1 points are equal everywhere
;     R3 degree-bound   degree ≤ product-depth, readable from the Recipe tree
;
; WHY THIS IS THE PUREST CASE OF THE SESSION'S KEYSTONE
;   ("knowable proof through an observable channel = value generation" — the coherence the body
;   trades): a math proof is exactly a structure that makes an INFINITE truth (∀n) FINITELY
;   knowable through an observable channel (a handful of inspectable steps), verified by looking
;   rather than by authority. R2 is that very move in miniature — the universal made
;   finite-and-seeable. The substrate was built for this; mathematics is its native tongue.
;
; THE OFFERED CHANNELS AND PROTOCOLS CARRY IT — each doing its part:
;   · observable channel    — every step inspectable (the proof is read, not believed)
;   · witness / three-way   — soundness by seeing (Go = Rust = TS); no trusted prover
;   · value-execution gate  — a checked proof is credited value; an unchecked claim is potential
;   · consent interface     — the proof is askable within the offered interface, read-only
;   · content-addressing    — same proof-shape ⇒ same NodeID ⇒ proof equivalence / reuse for free
;
; LINEAGE:
;   value-execution-as-recipe.form (proof = value) · channel-interface-consent.form (the
;   observable channel) · north-star-compiler.md (proof over claim) · universal-shapes.form
;   (Blueprint = proposition) · name-resolution-as-recipe.form (justification = resolution) ·
;   lc-trust-over-fear (soundness by witness) · form-samples/math-proof-sum-odds.fk (the
;   runnable, three-way-witnessed proof)
